Source: thaifonts-scalable
Section: x11
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Theppitak Karoonboonyanan <thep@linux.thai.net>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 5.0.35)
Build-Depends-Indep: defoma (>= 0.7.0), fontforge|pfaedit, xfonts-utils|ttmkfdir
Standards-Version: 3.7.2

Package: t1-thai-tlwg
Architecture: all
Depends: defoma, xfonts-utils (>= 1:1.0.0-4)
Description: Thai fonts in Type1 format
 This package provides some free-licensed fonts that are
 enhanced by developpers from Thai Linux Working Group.
 In Type1 format.
 .
 At the moment there are three families from the National Font
 Project included here:
  - Garuda
  - Norasi
 one from NECTEC:
  - Loma
 and three developed by TLWG itself:
  - Tlwg Mono
  - Tlwg Typewriter
  - Purisa

Package: ttf-thai-tlwg
Architecture: all
Depends: defoma, x-ttcidfont-conf
Replaces: xfonts-thai-ttf
Description: Thai fonts in TrueType format
 This package provides some free-licensed fonts that are
 enhanced by developpers from Thai Linux Working Group.
 In TrueType format.
 .
 At the moment there are three families from the National Font
 Project included here:
  - Garuda
  - Norasi
 one from NECTEC:
  - Loma
 and three developed by TLWG itself:
  - Tlwg Mono
  - Tlwg Typewriter
  - Purisa

Package: xfonts-thai-ttf
Architecture: all
Pre-Depends: ttf-thai-tlwg
Description: Thai TrueType fonts (transitional package)
 Dummy package for smooth upgrade to ttf-thai-tlwg, can be safely removed.

